Former Lagos State Governor, Bola Tinubu is currently leading by a wide margin at the ongoing Presidential primary of the All Progressives Congress in Abuja.Tinubu has polled 1070 votes so far, according to a tweet by Bashir Ahmad, former new media aide to President Muhammadu Buhari. Rotimi Amaechi, former Minister of Transportation scored 238 votes which, shows a clear huge gap between Tinubu and his opponents.Amaechi is closely followed by Vice-President Yemi Osinbajo who scored 177 votes.  UPDATE: 11:37AMBola Ahmed Tinubu 1070Rotimi Amaechi 238Yemi Osibanjo 177Ahmed Lawal 102Yahaya Bello 25Dave Umahi 20Ben Ayade 21Ahmed Sani 3Void Votes 8#APCSpecialConvention  #APCPresidentialPrimaries 